# Rival pinned models — one OpenRouter model ID per line.
# These bypass the :free filter and always rank first (in file order) in ~/.rival/models.json.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines ignored.
#
# Discovery still enforces MIN_CONTEXT and runs a health-check ping against each.
# If a pinned model fails resolution or health-check, discovery logs a warning and continues.
#
# To enable: copy this file to ~/.rival/pinned.txt and uncomment / edit the lines you want.
#   mkdir -p ~/.rival && cp pinned.txt.example ~/.rival/pinned.txt
#
# Recommended elite tri-corpus chain for sequential `--panel` (max training-corpus diversity):
#   Slot 1: wide first-pass caster
#   Slot 2: code+reasoning validator from a different family
#   Slot 3: code-tuned final judge from a third family
#
# x-ai/grok-4.1-fast
# deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro
# openai/gpt-5.1-codex
